blocks.text: <bold>Tottenham Hotspur</bold> and England midfielder Dele Alli, 24, is "pushing" for a move to French champions <bold>Paris St-Germain</bold> but negotiations are proving difficult. <link><caption>(Italian journalist Fabrizio Romano, on Twitter)</caption><url href="https://twitter.com/FabrizioRomano/status/1350792928453541888" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Manchester City</bold> manager Pep Guardiola will have £200m to spend in the summer, with <bold>Inter Milan's</bold> Belgium and former Manchester United striker Romelu Lukaku, 27, on a list of potential signings. <link><caption>(Telegraph - subscription required)</caption><url href="https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/01/16/pep-guardiola-oversee-man-citys-200m-summer-transfer-spree/" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Sheffield United</bold> remain confident they can sign England midfielder Jesse Lingard, 28, from <bold>Manchester United,</bold> despite their position at the bottom of the Premier League. <link><caption>(Sheffield Star)</caption><url href="https://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/sheffield-united/sheffield-united-set-step-their-pursuit-manchester-united-star-3103530" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>West Ham United </bold>are weighing up a move for <bold>Montpellier's </bold>26-year-old French striker Gaetan Laborde.<link><caption>(Telegraph - subscription required)</caption><url href="https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/01/17/mike-mcgraths-transfer-notebookwest-ham-considering-move-montpellier/" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Barcelona</bold> acting president Carles Tusquets suggested signing <bold>Manchester City</bold> and Spain defender Eric Garcia, 20, for 8m euros (£7.1m) to the club's three presidential candidates, but any move could not go ahead as not all of them were in agreement. <link><caption>(Marca)  </caption><url href="https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2021/01/17/6003698922601d6d5e8b457d.html" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Everton </bold>have cooled their interest in <bold>Bournemouth </bold>striker Joshua King, 29, with the Norway international said to be looking for a £120,000-a-week deal. <link><caption>(Sun)</caption><url href="https://www.thesun.co.uk/sport/football/13763021/josh-king-transfer-everton-bournemouth-contract/" platform="highweb"/></link>

elements.altText: Manchester United players look dejected at Anfield in January last year
elements.caption: Manchester United players looked dejected at Anfield in January last year, but they have closed the gap significantly in just 12 months

elements.text: <link><caption>How Anfield draw underlines Man Utd progress</caption><url href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55699252" platform="highweb"/></link>

blocks.text: Netherlands forward Memphis Depay, 26, says he and <bold>Lyon</bold> team-mate Houssem Aouar, 22, want to move to "one of the top three clubs in the world". Depay has been linked with <bold>Barcelona,</bold> while French midfielder Aouar was reported to be a target for <bold>Arsenal. </bold><link><caption>(Canal+)</caption><url href="https://www.canalplus.com/" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Marseille</bold> manager Andre Villas-Boas has confirmed that French midfielder Morgan Sanson is a target for English teams, with <bold>Arsenal, Aston Villa, Tottenham</bold> and <bold>West Ham</bold> linked with the 26-year-old. <link><caption>(Mail) </caption><url href="https://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-9156487/Marseille-boss-Andre-Villas-Boas-confirms-Premier-League-Morgan-Sanson.html" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Inter Milan</bold> director Beppe Marotta says the Serie A side are financially stable but will not be making "any investments" during the January transfer window. <link><caption>(Sky Sport Italia - in Italian)</caption><url href="https://sport.sky.it/calciomercato/2021/01/13/cessione-inter-marotta-intervista" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Norwich City </bold>are set to sign Greece left-back Dimitris Giannoulis, 25, from <bold>PAOK </bold>for a fee which could rise to 7m euros (£6.2m). <link><caption>(Pink Un)</caption><url href="https://www.pinkun.com/sport/norwich-city/canaries-dimitris-giannoulis-poak-transfer-latest-6910464" platform="highweb"/></link>

<bold>Hull City</bold> manager Grant McCann says English striker Keane Lewis-Potter is not for sale, despite talks over a new deal for the 19-year-old reaching an impasse. <link><caption>(Yorkshire Post)</caption><url href="https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/sport/football/hull-city/keane-lewis-potter-not-sale-insists-hull-city-boss-grant-mccann-3103573" platform="highweb"/></link>
